---
description: Secrets and credential handling
alwaysApply: true
---

Never commit `.env` files, API keys, or tokens. `.env.local` is gitignored;
`.env.local.example` documents required variables with empty values only —
keep it that way when adding new ones.

`BLOG_CONTENT_TOKEN` is a GitHub personal access token, read-only, scoped to
the private `mllws-blog` repo — treat it like any other secret: reference it
only via `process.env.BLOG_CONTENT_TOKEN`, never log its value, never print
it in error messages.

This repo is public. Assume anything committed is permanently public, even
if deleted in a later commit — git history doesn't forget. When in doubt
about whether something is sensitive, don't commit it and ask first.
